Project Bureau — ATF1502BE Block B Product Terms

Project Bureau aims at documenting the bitstream format of Microchip ATF15xx CPLDs. This is a work in progress. See more in the repository.

Product Term Array Configuration Bitmap

Logic block B uses 7680 (known) fuses within range 0..15360 for product terms MC17.PT1, MC17.PT2, MC17.PT3, MC17.PT4, MC17.PT5, MC18.PT1, MC18.PT2, MC18.PT3, MC18.PT4, MC18.PT5, MC19.PT1, MC19.PT2, MC19.PT3, MC19.PT4, MC19.PT5, MC20.PT1, MC20.PT2, MC20.PT3, MC20.PT4, MC20.PT5, MC21.PT1, MC21.PT2, MC21.PT3, MC21.PT4, MC21.PT5, MC22.PT1, MC22.PT2, MC22.PT3, MC22.PT4, MC22.PT5, MC23.PT1, MC23.PT2, MC23.PT3, MC23.PT4, MC23.PT5, MC24.PT1, MC24.PT2, MC24.PT3, MC24.PT4, MC24.PT5, MC25.PT1, MC25.PT2, MC25.PT3, MC25.PT4, MC25.PT5, MC26.PT1, MC26.PT2, MC26.PT3, MC26.PT4, MC26.PT5, MC27.PT1, MC27.PT2, MC27.PT3, MC27.PT4, MC27.PT5, MC28.PT1, MC28.PT2, MC28.PT3, MC28.PT4, MC28.PT5, MC29.PT1, MC29.PT2, MC29.PT3, MC29.PT4, MC29.PT5, MC30.PT1, MC30.PT2, MC30.PT3, MC30.PT4, MC30.PT5, MC31.PT1, MC31.PT2, MC31.PT3, MC31.PT4, MC31.PT5, MC32.PT1, MC32.PT2, MC32.PT3, MC32.PT4, MC32.PT5.
